&lt;p&gt;More than 22M people living with cancer have behavioral health needs such as anxiety, depression, and distress.&amp;nbsp; We integrate with oncology practices and health systems through the Collaborative Care Model (CoCM) to wrap our members with a behavioral health team, care programming, and outcomes analysis.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Collaborative Care Model is an evidence-based clinical model that has been shown to successfully improve mild to moderate behavioral health needs more effectively than the current standard of care. With &amp;nbsp;program customized to our members, we will be able to improve our members’ behavioral health above and beyond traditional CoCM models.&lt;/p&gt;
